n style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/housing.html\">Supportive Housing</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/employs.html\">Employment Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/consultation.html\">Consultation and Technical Assistance</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/vulnerability.html\">Vulnerability Assessment Tool</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"alignc boldtxt top30\" style=\"margin: 30px auto 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Client: Gary</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><img title=\"Gary\" src=\"http://desc.org/images/clients/Gary1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Gary, a Vietnam era veteran who lived in downtown doorways and alleys for over 4 years while dealing with mental illness and alcoholism is thrilled to be living in supportive housing at 1811 Eastlake. Gary's participation in support groups, counseling, and community activities has helped him dramatically reduce his alcohol consumption and stabilize his life.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><em>Photo credit: David Entrikin &copy; 2009</em></p>"},
  {title: "Clinical services", body: "<h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.5rem 0px; color: #41887a; font-size: 3rem; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.4; background-color: #fefefe;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px;\">Clinical Services</span></h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">DESC clients live with severe and often untreated mental illness, addictive disorders, and a host of other physical and developmental disabilities that have caused or contributed to their chronic homelessness. By addressing each client's unique series of problems through a structured and comprehensive recovery plan, staff are able to help clients stabilize and reclaim their lives. Engagement in our highly effective, state-licensed mental health and chemical dependency treatment programs contribute to client's success in housing.</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">HOST</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">HOST (Homeless Outreach Stabilization and Transition) case managers \"take to the streets\" where they provide outreach and intensive case management there and in shelters, hospitals, jails, libraries and other facilities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">By seeking out mentally ill and homeless people in this way, HOST outreach staff develop trusting relationships that encourage new clients to begin seeking assistance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">At DESC's mental health drop-in center, men and women can become familiar with the environment at their own pace. When they are ready, case managers will help identify their underlying issues and service needs, facilitate access to these services (whether at DESC or with other service providers), help achieve clinical and social stabilization, secure housing, and transition them into mental health treatment and long-term case management.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"bolddef\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\" href=\"http://desc.org/host.html\">more</a></span></p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">SAGE</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">SAGE, which stands for Support, Advocacy, Growth, and Employment, is the ongoing comprehensive case management component of DESC's mental health program.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">SAGE case managers work with clients to help them secure and maintain housing and improve their clinical and social stability, thus enhancing their level of independence and self-sufficiency. This program has over 1,000 clients currently enrolled.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"bolddef\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\" href=\"http://desc.org/sage.html\">more</a></span></p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">Chemical Dependency Treatment</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Many clients have a sustained and/or complicated substance abuse history in addition to their co-occurring mental disorder. Often people suffering from mental illness who lack access to psychiatric treatment, attempt to self-medicate with street drugs or alcohol to lessen the symptoms.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The ability to provide highly integrated services to people with concurrent mental health and substance-use disorder concerns is rare among homeless service providers. At DESC, our network of clinical services allow counselors to work in coordination with mental health case managers in both the emergency shelter and in supportive housing projects so that services meet clients at their current level and offer the support that can lead to significant change.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Assessment hours for substance-use disorder treatment services are available on a first come first served basis on the following schedule::</p>\r\n<blockquote style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">\r\n<p>1:00PM - 2:30PM on Mondays and Wednesday; and 9:00AM - 10:30AM on Friday at 216 James Street office in Seattle's Pioneer Square neighborhood.</p>\r\n<p>9:00AM - 10:30AM on Tuesdays &amp; Thursdays at 222 Wall Street, Suite 100 in Seattle's Belltown neighborhood.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">DESC is a King County Drug Court provider.</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">Crisis Respite Program</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Working in partnership with Harborview Medical Center, King County Mental Health Court, and hospitals across the county, the Crisis Respite Program is a vital buffer between psychiatric emergency care and life back on the streets.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">It provides severely mentally ill homeless men and women, just emerging from a recent crisis or jail, a chance to stabilize in safe, secure and supportive surroundings and connect with services and housing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Without this program, these people would have little choice but to return to the streets, where they would most likely repeat a cycle of using costly public services like emergency rooms, jails, sobering centers and courts.</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">Crisis Solutions Center</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The Crisis Solutions Center (CSC) provides a new resource for police, medics, crisis mental health professionals, and other first responders to use for individuals who are in crisis and might otherwise receive no help, or be taken to jail or a hospital emergency department. The goal of the CSC is to reduce chronic homelessness and unnecessary involvement in the criminal justice and emergency medical systems.<span style=\"color: #41887a;\">&nbsp;<a class=\"bolddef\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\" href=\"http://desc.org/crisis_solutions.html\">more</a></span></p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">PACT</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">DESC is honored to be one of the few agencies in Washington to deliver a Program of Assertive Community Treatment (PACT).</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">PACT is a nationally recognized practice that works with people who suffer from serious and persistent mental illness, assisting them in their journey towards recovery.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">The PACT model is distinguished by its intensive outreach and team-oriented, trans-disciplinary approach.&nbsp;<a class=\"bolddef\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\" href=\"http://desc.org/home.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">more</a></p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">HOME</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">DESC's Housing Opportunities and Meaningful Engagement (HOME) program is funded by a federal grant from the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA)&nbsp;<span data-ft=\"{'tn':'K'}\">2014 Grants for the Benefit of Homeless Individuals-Services in Supportive Housing&nbsp;</span>for a period of three years beginning October 1, 2014.&nbsp; The HOME team will engage homeless veterans and chronically homeless individuals with substance use or co-occurring substance use disorders and mental illness into services and supportive housing. The goal of the program is to engage, stably house and make needed services and treatment available to chronically homeless individuals identified as Long Term Shelter Stayes (LTSS) in Seattle and King County.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"bolddef\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\" href=\"http://desc.org/home.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">more</a></span></p>", sidebar: "<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/whoweserve_videopage.html\">Who We Serve</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/entry.html\">Entry Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/housing.html\">Supportive Housing</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/employs.html\">Employment Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/consultation.html\">Consultation and Technical Assistance</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/vulnerability.html\">Vulnerability Assessment Tool</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"top30 alignc boldtxt\" style=\"margin: 30px auto 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Client: Charles</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: center;\" title=\"Charles\" src=\"http://desc.org/images/clients/Charles1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">\"Never thought I'd live this long, being out on the streets and sick for all them years. Used to go to bed at night on a piece of cardboard in an alley; never knowing if I'd wake up in the morning or not. Today I wake up in my own bed in my own apartment. I go downstairs and have breakfast with other people like me who are just trying to get their lives together and maybe do something good for somebody else who needs help. The folks at DESC showed me how.\"</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><em>Client photo courtesy of photographer David Entrikin &copy; 2009</em></p>"},
  {title: "Consultation and Tech", body: "<h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.5rem 0px; color: #41887a; font-size: 3rem; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.4; background-color: #fefefe;\">Consultation and Technical Assistance</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", sidebar: "sidebar"},
  {title: "title", body: "<h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.5rem 0px; color: #41887a; font-size: 3rem; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.4; background-color: #fefefe;\">Get Involved</h1>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Ending homelessness is&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;a mystery. Experience proves that placing homeless men and women in housing supported by trained staff with a complement of health care, chemical dependency treatment, and mental health services keeps even the most vulnerable and disabled adults off of the streets and safely housed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">We also know that the type of programs offered by DESC actually cost less than allowing people to remain homeless. The result is fewer tax dollars spent.&nbsp;<strong>Everyone benefits!</strong></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"smallheading\" style=\"font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #41887a; margin-top: 30px; margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">If you believe that homelessness can be eliminated, you can:</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">\r\n<li>donate</li>\r\n<li>volunteer</li>\r\n<li>attend an event</li>\r\n<li>advocate</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"col1\" style=\"width: 630px; float: left; font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">If you have questions about making a donation or would like to speak to someone about making one, please contact&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"mailto:mmayes@desc.org\">Megan Mayes</a></span>, Director of Development, at 206-515-1553.</p>", sidebar: "<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/donate.html\">Donate</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/volunteer.html\">Volunteer</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/events.html\">Events</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/political.html\">Advocate</a></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"top30 alignc boldtxt\" style=\"margin: 30px auto 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Client: Jerome</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; text-align: center;\" title=\"Jerome\" src=\"http://desc.org/images/clients/Jerome1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\">Jerome has experienced homelessness off an on for 35 years while suffering from mental illness and alcohol addiction. In 2001 he found a home in the Lyon Building and has been a notable cheery, self-reliant, and often employed resident ever since. Jerome is well liked by all who work with him.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><em>Client photo courtesy of photographer David Entrikin &copy; 2009</em></p>"},
  {title: "who we serve", body: "<h1 style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0.5rem 0px; color: #41887a; font-size: 3rem; padding: 0px; font-family: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; text-rendering: optimizeLegibility; line-height: 1.4; background-color: #fefefe;\">Who We Serve</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">You can learn about who DESC serves through these videos. You can also see many of DESC's videos on&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/user4507921\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Vimeo</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a href=\"http://storyclock.me/doors/\"><img src=\"http://desc.org/images/DESC-Breakfast%20of%20Champions%202016_VR%20viewer.jpg\" alt=\"DESC 2016 Breakfast of Champions VR film\" width=\"787\" height=\"703\" longdesc=\"http://desc.org/images/DESC-Breakfast%20of%20Champions%202016_VR%20viewer.jpg\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" href=\"https://youtu.be/a3XrTb3uZzs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The Virtual Reality of Housing First: A 360&ordm; Journey</a>&nbsp;</span>Take a 360&ordm; journey through one man's life as he moves from living outdoors on the streets of Seattle to his Housing First unit in DESC's permanent supportive housing program. To view in VR format (virtual reality), you will need a headset, a VR gear/viewer like Google Cardboard, Oculus, etc.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #41887a; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\" href=\"https://youtu.be/jVUpj1SLbmI\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jVUpj1SLbmI\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"https://youtu.be/jVUpj1SLbmI\">2016 DESC documentary - \"Paper Horns\"</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/109152062\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/109152062\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">IMAGINE: A World WIthout Homelessness</a></span>&nbsp;Success stories and challenges through the eyes of clients who DESC serve.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/77632266\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"https://vimeo.com/77632266\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Roger's Story - A Life Reclaimed</a></span>&nbsp;tells Roger's story of addiction and homelessness and how with DESC's help, he overcame his obstacles and began life anew.</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/51624836?title=1&amp;byline=1&amp;portrait=1\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" href=\"https://vimeo.com/51624836\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DESC's Building Blocks</a>&nbsp;</span>shows how DESC provides the building blocks to end chronic homelessness through providing security, community, self worth and hope.</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/51306736?title=1&amp;byline=1&amp;portrait=1\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/51306736\">Making Her Way Back</a></span>&nbsp;tells the story of DESC resident Cheena and how with the help of DESC she has made her way back from homelessness to a stable life in her own home.</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/30958692?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #41887a;\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/30958692\"><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">Not All Superheroes Wear Capes</span>&nbsp;</a>chronicles the story of superhero Jon, DESC client, who moves through our programs and on to a self sustaining life. Along the way we learn of other superheroes: volunteers and donors, who join in the fight to end homelessness.</p>\r\n<p><iframe style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\" src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/17615880?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/17615880\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">DESC in 3D: A Documentary</a></span>&nbsp;from 2010 was presented at our 2nd annual fund-raising gala chronicling how we serve the most vulnerable homeless population: those who are mentally disabled and chronically addicted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/14870312?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"320\" height=\"180\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #41887a;\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/14870312\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><span style=\"color: #41887a;\">Where They Are</span></a>&nbsp;from 2009 is a docuportrait by NonFiction Media commissioned by DESC for our 30th Anniversary in November, 2009. This video shares a range of our clients' stories, illustrating how we touch the lives of those we serve.</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><iframe src=\"http://player.vimeo.com/video/14308267?title=0&amp;byline=0&amp;portrait=0\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/14308267\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">1811 Eastlake</a></span>&nbsp;from<span style=\"color: #41887a;\">&nbsp;<a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/user3381546\">Ryan McNamee</a>&nbsp;</span>on<span style=\"color: #41887a;\">&nbsp;<a class=\"greenlink\" style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" href=\"http://vimeo.com/\">Vimeo</a></span>. This is an inside look at Downtown Emergency Service Center's 1811 Eastlake project and the Housing First Philosophy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", sidebar: "<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/entry.html\">Entry Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/clinical.html\">Clinical Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/housing.html\">Supportive Housing</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/employs.html\">Employment Services</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/consultation.html\">Consultation and Technical Assistance</a></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom: 10px; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #41887a; font-size: 12pt;\"><a class=\"greenlink\" href=\"http://desc.org/vulnerability.html\">Vulnerability Assessment Tool</a></span></p>"}
])
